1 TITL France, Deaths
1 PUBL MyHeritage
1 TEXT The number of deaths reported and contained in this collection for the years 1970 and 1971 are well below expected counts and this is likely due to a ramp-up in compliance by local French offices repo
2 CONC rting deaths to INSEE during these two years. In this collection the number of deaths reported for 1970 appear to be only about 8% of actual and for 1971 the number is about 50% of actual. By 1972 nea
2 CONC rly comprehensive reporting was achieved across France and its territories.</p>
2 CONC </p>While most of the birthplaces and deathplaces are in France there are over 2.5 million records in this collection of persons who were born or died in other countries -- with neighboring and nearby
2 CONC  countries (such as Belgium, Germany, Spain, Italy, and Poland) and countries which were former French colonies (such as Algeria, Morocco, Tunisia, Madagascar, and Vietnam) being most common.</p>
2 CONC </p>This collection will be updated regularly as additional records are released.
