1 TITL Auschwitz Death Certificates, 1941-1943
1 PUBL MyHeritage
1 TEXT This collection covers nearly 65,000 individuals, the majority of which were either Roman Catholic or Jewish. Please note, only individuals who were registered prisoners in the camp were recorded in t
2 CONC he death certificate books. According to the Auschwitz-Birkenau State Museum, the estimated number of victims who perished in Auschwitz between 1940 and 1945 is between 1.1 million and 1.5 million peo
2 CONC ple. The majority of these victims were killed immediately upon arrival, and were never officially registered in the German record books. Thus, their deaths were not recorded. This collection provides
2 CONC  information on just a small percentage of the deaths that occurred at Auschwitz.
1 _TYPE Collection
1 _MEDI 10460
0 @S500143@ SOUR
1 _UPD 16 APR 2023 05:35:25 GMT -0500 
