1 TITL Germany, Hesse, Deaths
1 PUBL MyHeritage
1 TEXT Dated from October 1874, state appointed registrars of death records of all inhabitants of Prussia, which include many of the communities in this collection. Civil Registry records from Hessian commun
2 CONC ities that were not part of Prussia begin as early as January 1876. While churches continued to keep traditional records, the State also mandated that the personal or marital status of the entire popu
2 CONC lation be recorded. These records were indexed and made searchable by MyHeritage.
