1 TITL 1930 United States Federal Census
1 PUBL MyHeritage
1 TEXT The 1930 Census determined the population of the United States to be 122,775,046. This is an increase of almost 16 percent over the 1920 Census, which reported a population of 106,021,537. This was th
2 CONC e 15th decennial census conducted in the United States under authority granted by Article I, Section 2 of the United States Constitution. It was conducted in April 1930, except in Alaska, where it was
2 CONC  conducted in late 1929. Until 2012 the 1930 Census is the latest available to the public, due to 72-year privacy laws. It is based on actual counts of persons living in residential structures.
1 _TYPE Collection
1 _MEDI 10134
0 @S500202@ SOUR
1 _UPD 5 MAY 2023 16:28:12 GMT -0500 
1 TITL Connecticut, Marriages, 1966-2002
1 PUBL MyHeritage
1 TEXT <p>In addition to the genealogical information this index provides about the marriage, these records can be useful in requesting the original marriage licenses from which this index is derived. Additi
2 CONC onal information is usually available on the original documents and may list the bride's and groom's birthplace and the names and birthplaces of their parents. Copies of original marriage records can 
2 CONC be obtained from the <A href="http://www.ct.gov/dPh/cwp/view.asp?a=3132&q=388130&dphNav=</p><p>46940</p>&dphNav_GID=1601" target="_blank">Connecticut Department of Public Health</a> for a fee.
